The '''Armenians in Abkhazia''' form the second largest ethnic group in [[Abkhazia]] after the native [[Abkhazians]].<ref>[http://www.iwpr.net/?s=f&o=257748&p=crs&l=EN&apc_state=hena-Abkhazia_2______publish_date_1_10_compact_11 Abkhazia Offers Citizenship to Diaspora]. [[Institute for War and Peace Reporting|IWPR]]. CRS No. 314, 10-Nov-05; V.A. Chirikba. Armenians and their Dialects in Abkhazia. In: ''Evidence and Counter-Evidence, Festschrift Frederik Kortlandt'', Volume 2, SSGL 33, Amsterdam - New York: Rodopi, p. 51-67.</ref> Armenians settled in Abkhazia in late 19th and the early 20th centuries and are now the largest ethnic group in [[Sukhumi district|Sukhumi]], [[Gulripsh district|Gulripsh]] and [[Gagra district]]s forming 20% of the Abkhazian population with approximately 42,000 out of a total of 242,862.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citypopulation.de/Georgia.html |title=Georgia |publisher=Citypopulation |date=2012-01-01 |accessdate=2012-12-20}}</ref>
